description:
&lt;p&gt;The seven integrated regions of our joint enterprise will work with local systems to support and improve how care is provided to patients and communities. These regions will be supported by the corporate centre providing expertise and developing policy. The focus will be on guiding and managing the delivery of services through local integrated health systems, sustainability and transformation partnerships, and devolution areas&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has become available within Medical Directorate North and East Yorkshire Region as – Digital Primary Care Band 8b(Care Homes)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Digital Primary Care Programme Lead, the post holder will work as part of a dynamic team in delivering strategic advice to senior leaders across the region to coordinate a variety of approaches to planning and investment in digitally enabled services, including a programme assurance approach to the adoption and uptake of core digital services that need to be implemented ubiquitously and a more agile and iterative approach to transformation programmes and accelerators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will develop effective programme management, business and portfolio management, working closely with colleagues across the sector, ensuring a coherent approach and supporting and ensuring alignment across the system&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will work as part of a matrix with NHSx, NHS Digital, local CCG, Provider Trusts, CSU’s and other Digital/Informatics delivery colleagues, providing professional advice and interpreting complex information in the translation of policy, standards, statutory and regulatory requirements to deliver the Long-Term Plan&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder is responsible for putting in place effective mechanisms to support, manage and assure system investments in digital across a range of funding streams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will define current processes, facilitate discussions and advise colleagues as to how best practice might be adopted in the future and providing professional expertise to the outcome of the business processes for the Department or Directorate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will lead the provision of an efficient, effective and high quality professional and well-coordinated digital primary care transformation service capable of meeting all statutory, regulatory and NHS requirements ensuring alignment with the activity of the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will also be responsible for building effective working relationships with local CCG and CSU colleagues, providing, as necessary, professional advice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will be expected to contribute to regional functional leadership as part of a dynamic team delivering an effective service, supporting managers and staff across the Digital Primary Care Transformation Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about the role please refer to the attached Job Description &amp; Specifications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Kerry Wheeler&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Senior Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Kerry.Wheeler@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
